                                        <h3 class="highlight header-colorize text-uppercase mb-4 mt-3"><a href="https://www.marshall.edu/academics/programs/geology-bs/">Geology, B.S.</a></h3>
                                        <p class="mb-4 size-18">If you think Geology is just collecting and identifying rocks, you could be missing out on an exciting opportunity to major in a dynamic field and build a solid career that has real impact on our world.</p>
                                        <p class="mb-4 size-18">Geology, also known as Geoscience, focuses on the study of the earth’s composition, internal structure, processes and history. Geology majors prepare to address vital issues that affect our planet and its people. </p>
                                        <p class="mb-4 size-18">The Earth’s expanding population and increased use of natural resources along with our need for energy, environmental protection and responsible land and resource management are areas that need more Geology majors and future geoscientists well into the future. Employment for geoscientists is predicted to grow 5 percent through 2029, faster than the average for all other occupations.</p>
                                        <h4 class="header-colorize">Why study Geology at Marshall University?</h4>
                                        <p class="mb-4 size-18">Geology majors benefit from a wealth of opportunity starting with Marshall University’s location in southern West Virginia. This area enables Marshall students to take advantage of field-based studies in Environmental Geoscience and Engineering Geology, and learn firsthand about energy resources. West Virginia is currently the 2nd largest producer of coal; 4th largest producer of energy in the United States; and 8th largest producer of natural gas. The Geology program offers an average of three field trips each semester that are either day-long or overnight to see and study local and regional geology in West Virginia and nearby states.</p>
                                        <a href="https://www.marshall.edu/academics/programs/geology-bs/" class="learn-more size-15">Learn more <span class="ml-2 right-icon"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i></span></a>
